<subSubSection id="C317ABC4D97E7A2EFF2CFA9AFAD0DBDA" pageId="15" pageNumber="538" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB2F84FD97E7A2EFF2CFA9AFAD0DBDA" blockId="15.[151,1436,1304,1475]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis id="B979245DD97E7A2EFF2CFA9AFED9DB62" bold="true" box="[199,322,1376,1403]" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body very flattened dorso-ventrally; prothorax with lateral tubercles distinctly acute, placed in the posterior third, the apex directed backward; pronotum without tubercles; elytra without centrobasal crest or longitudinal carina; basal metatarsomere longer than next two together. Number of species currently included: 3.
</paragraph>
